                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-05-11</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Okay for discussing general ideas, but not much real world use. There's not a lot to be had from this book. They cover too much and discuss too much generalized topics and never really touch on any real-world working, intelligent firewall fules and uses. Just too much generalized fluff. You'll get more from a 'man page' on iptables and be able to put it to use, at least, compared to this. It is interesting, but there's too much generalization and fluff and not much someone can *use* from it.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">very good book for networkers to understand security</div>
